Amorphous Androgynous Biography by allmusic.com.



Biography by Sean Cooper


One year before Garry Cobain and Brian Dougans released Lifeforms, their breakthrough album as Future Sound of London, the duo recorded Tales of Ephidrena as Amorphous Androgynous. Charting an intriguing fusion of industrial techno with the free-form organic passages that would become the norm in ambient techno several years later, Tales of Ephidrena was the first hint of what was to become the trademark sound of FSOL.

Alice In Ultraland album review from Discogs.com



Review by xenlab,



Best album I&#039;ve heard in a long long time.

I knew it was going to be good as soon as the first piano chord struck.... but by the time the vocals come in on the 2nd track &#039;The Witchfinder&#039; you are so engulfed in the psychedelic ambience that the funky chorus almost blind sides you... and it only gets better from there.

This one is going to be in my rotation for a long time. Probably the most brilliant thing Brian Dougans & Garry Cobain have ever done, IMHO.
